The Democratic Alliance applied in the Western Cape High Court to have the SABC's group executive of corporate affairs, Hlaudi Motsoeneng, declared as someone who cannot occupy a position of trust. On Monday, Judge Owen Rodgers ruled that Motsoeneng could not hold any position at the public broadcaster unless the public protector's report into his appointment was set aside, or a disciplinary committee found in his favour. #Motsoeneng not entitled to hold any positon in the SABC unless + until the PP report is set aside or a new DC finds in his favour @News24  #Tugwana's appointment set aside. Her decisions as COO not invalid #Motsoeneng @News24  This story is developing.